{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"66a45bc92fe506e7","type":"text","text":"#  `<table>` Tag and Structure\n\n* The `<table>` tag defines a **data table** with rows and columns.\n* **Default ARIA role** is `table`. Use:\n\n  * `role=\"grid\"` for selectable or navigable tables.\n  * `role=\"treegrid\"` for expandable/collapsible rows.\n\n---\n\n### 📚 Table Content Order (All optional but recommended):\n\n1. `<caption>` – Describes the table.\n2. `<colgroup>` – Groups columns; may contain `<col>`.\n3. `<thead>` – Header rows.\n4. `<tbody>` – Main data rows.\n5. `<tfoot>` – Footer rows.\n\n---\n\n### 🔸 Row & Cell Structure:\n\n* Rows: `<tr>`\n* Header cells: `<th>`\n* Data cells: `<td>`\n\nThese elements hold the actual table content.","x":-125,"y":-30,"width":645,"height":690},
		{"id":"a6e2c55f13ccf8e9","type":"text","text":"### 📌 `<caption>` \n\nThe `<caption>` element provides a **title or description** for a table.\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Purpose:\n\n* Helps users **understand what the table is about**.\n* Displayed **above the table** by default.\n* Read by **screen readers**, improving accessibility.\n\n---\n\n### 📖 Example:\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <caption>Monthly Sales Report</caption>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Month</th>\n      <th>Sales</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>January</td>\n      <td>$10,000</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📝 Notes:\n\n* Only **one `<caption>`** is allowed per table.\n* Place it **immediately after the `<table>` tag**, before `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, etc.\n* You can style it with CSS using `caption-side: top | bottom`.","x":840,"y":-930,"width":520,"height":900},
		{"id":"a3e6dd4aba935190","type":"text","text":"### 📚 `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, and `<tfoot>`\n\nThese elements help **organize** and **structure** your table into **logical sections**. They improve **accessibility**, **styling**, and **data manipulation**.\n\n---\n\n### 🔷 `<thead>`\n\n* Contains the **table’s header row(s)**.\n* Usually includes `<tr>` with `<th>` cells.\n* Helps screen readers and makes styling easier.\n\n```html\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Item</th>\n    <th>Price</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🔶 `<tbody>`\n\n* Contains the **main data** of the table.\n* Includes one or more `<tr>` with `<td>` cells.\n* Can have multiple `<tbody>` sections (rarely used).\n\n```html\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Apple</td>\n    <td>$1.00</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🔸 `<tfoot>`\n\n* Holds **summary or footer** rows (like totals).\n* Often placed **before `<tbody>`** in the HTML for better rendering during page load, but shown **below** the data visually.\n\n```html\n<tfoot>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Total</td>\n    <td>$15.00</td>\n  </tr>\n</tfoot>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📝 Why Use These?\n\n* Improves **semantics** and **accessibility**.\n* Makes **styling** (e.g. sticky headers/footers) easier.\n* Useful for **JavaScript** operations like sorting/filtering.\n","x":840,"y":40,"width":520,"height":1280},
		{"id":"a47900d90c12f313","type":"text","text":"### 📄 Table Content\n\n* Tables are built with rows (`<tr>`) and cells:\n\n  * **Header cells**: `<th>`\n  * **Data cells**: `<td>`\n\n---\n\n### 🧱 Key Points:\n\n* **Headers, bodies, footers**:\n\n  * `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tfoot>` organize the table, but real content lives in rows and cells.\n\n* **Table structure**:\n\n  * Each `<tr>` holds one or more `<th>` or `<td>` elements.\n  * `<th>` is used for **header cells**, often rendered **bold** and **centered** by default.\n\n* **Semantics**:\n\n  * `<th>` cells carry **ARIA roles** like `rowheader` or `columnheader`.\n  * Use the `scope` attribute (e.g., `scope=\"col\"`, `scope=\"row\"`) to explicitly define header roles. Default values apply if not set.\n\n---\n\n### 🎨 Styling Notes:\n\n* Old HTML attributes like `cellpadding`, `cellspacing`, and `border` are **deprecated**.\n* Use **CSS**:\n\n  * `border-collapse`, `border-spacing` for layout\n  * `empty-cells: hide` to hide unused cells\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Example Usage:\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Year</th>\n      <th>Name</th>\n      <th>Major</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">1956</th>\n      <td>Lou Minious</td>\n      <td>Physics</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n```\n\nThis allows screen readers and browsers to retain accessibility and readability even when scrolling or when only parts of the table are visible.\n","x":-880,"y":-930,"width":520,"height":1240},
		{"id":"661a5276dfe91406","type":"text","text":"### 📄 Merging Cells in HTML Tables\n\nYou can merge **table cells** horizontally or vertically using:\n\n---\n\n### 🔁 Horizontal Merge: `colspan`\n\n* Merges multiple columns into **one cell**.\n* Syntax:\n\n  ```html\n  <td colspan=\"3\">Merged across 3 columns</td>\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 🔃 Vertical Merge: `rowspan`\n\n* Merges multiple rows into **one cell**.\n* Syntax:\n\n  ```html\n  <td rowspan=\"2\">Merged across 2 rows</td>\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Example:\n\n```html\n<table border=\"1\">\n  <tr>\n    <th rowspan=\"2\">Name</th>\n    <th colspan=\"2\">Score</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Math</th>\n    <th>Science</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Alice</td>\n    <td>90</td>\n    <td>95</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📌 Notes:\n\n* Both `colspan` and `rowspan` values must be **positive integers**.\n* Always check the layout to avoid unbalanced rows/columns.\n* Works with `<td>` and `<th>`.","x":-880,"y":680,"width":520,"height":1140},
		{"id":"7d7d14467e32cf0f","type":"text","text":"### 📚 `<colgroup>` and `<col>` in HTML Tables\n\nThe `<colgroup>` and `<col>` elements help you define **column-level styling or behavior** in an HTML table, especially when you want to apply the same style or attribute to a group of columns.\n\n---\n\n### 🧱 `<colgroup>`\n\n* Used to group one or more columns in a table.\n* Placed **right after** `<caption>` (if present) and **before** `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, or `<tfoot>`.\n\n**Syntax:**\n\n```html\n<colgroup>\n  <col>\n  <col>\n</colgroup>\n```\n\n* You can also use `<colgroup span=\"2\">` to apply the group settings to multiple columns without repeating `<col>`.\n\n---\n\n### 📌 `<col>`\n\n* Represents a **single column** within the `<colgroup>`.\n* Does **not contain content**, only attributes like `style`, `class`, or `width`.\n\n**Example:**\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <colgroup>\n    <col style=\"background-color: #f2f2f2;\">\n    <col span=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0;\">\n  </colgroup>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Product</th>\n    <th>Price</th>\n    <th>Stock</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Pen</td>\n    <td>$1</td>\n    <td>100</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📝 When to Use:\n\n* Apply styles (like background, width, border) to entire columns **without repeating** on every `<td>` or `<th>`.\n* Help with **accessibility and structure** for complex tables.","x":-62,"y":880,"width":520,"height":1280}
